# 01 - Any Run Susp-Clipboard and ClickFix Tags

## Intro

Just like how we used Any Run to review MalSpam submissions in "05 - Any Run MalSpam Investigations.md", we can use Any Run to review ClickFix events. 

## Any Run Filter

Return to [https://app.any.run/submissions#](https://app.any.run/submissions#) and set the Runtype filter to URL and the Tag filter to susp-clipboard just like in the snip below.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Next, review the results. See the snip below.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Review the submissions that are for URLs that look benign because they are likely compromised sites.

One example is this ClearFake submission for the compromised site hxxps[:]//sinkysbeergardenandgrill[.]co[.]uk: https://app.any.run/tasks/395bfd97-58f6-4173-bcd8-a67dbe992bf9. See the snip below. We're not analyzing it right now, we're just getting familiar with it.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Next, review this submission: [https://app.any.run/browses/cb10fc1d-1e64-4ea9-a770-939fc2aa27e6](https://app.any.run/browses/cb10fc1d-1e64-4ea9-a770-939fc2aa27e6). The submitter analyzed two URLs. The first was the SocGholish compromised URL hxxps[:]//proceduresolutionsmgmt[.]com/training/. See the snip below to see the SocGholish landing page. 

![](data:image/png;base64,)

This is not ClickFix, but the submission is tagged with susp-clipboard because of the next domain they reviewed. Next, review the submission a little later and observe them view the domain xpolkfsddlswwkjddsljsy[.]com. See the snip below to see a new ClickFix theme.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

That's it for now. 

## Summary

This was just a cursory glance to see what's out there, and to understand a simple Any Run Submission filter combination that can be used to monitor the threats.
